  "text": "For many questions concerning processes in ecoevolutionary biology, such as dispersal-or selectiondependent species diversification [CITATION_1] and community assembly [CITATION_2] , no analytical solutions are (yet) available. However, the outcome of processes can be simulated by utilizing a wide range of parameter values representing them. The set of parameters resulting in a simulated pattern that best resembles the observed one is then assumed to approximate the processes in question. Our newly developed distance-based STEPCAM approach is a relatively simple model that could be easily extended by making, for instance, dispersal limitation spatially or temporally explicit, but at the risk of overparameterization.",
